headline: KBRA Assigns Preliminary Ratings to J.P. Morgan Mortgage Trust 2025-12MPR (JPMMT 2025-12MPR)
summary: NEW YORK, December 19, 2025--KBRA assigns preliminary ratings to 11 classes of mortgage pass-through notes from J.P. Morgan Mortgage Trust 2025-12MPR (JPMMT 2025-12MPR). The pool comprises 344 first-lien, fixed rate residential mortgage loans with an aggregate principal balance of $449.5 million as of the cut-off date. The pool includes both non-agency (91.3%) and agency-eligible (8.7%) loans. The weighted average original credit score is 758, which is well within the prime mortgage range.

headline: Quest Diagnostics to Speak at the 44th Annual J.P. Morgan Healthcare Conference
